Traffic.RoadNetwork

Class Auto

  • java.lang.Object
    • Traffic.RoadNetwork.Auto

  • public class Auto
extends java.lang.Object
    The Auto class will represent the vehicle objects travelling on the lanes. For the purposes of the simulation, all vehicle move with a constant speed, i.e., during each tick of the simulation, a vehicle will move to the next block if it is empty else it remains in the same block. If the vehicle is in a traffic block, then additional rules apply. For vehicles on intersection blocks, there is also an option for the vehicles to turn left or right based on the traffic rules.
